    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="179"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 857.857/91</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Cork</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cork</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >Queenstown</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1917-03-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Norwegian bark <hi rend="italic">Storenes</hi>, Buenos Aires to Queenstown,
                    maize, attacked by submarine March 1, 18 miles off Kinsale. Torpedo fired
                    without warning, missed ship. Submarine then came up, ordered <pb facs="0332"
                        n="160" xml:id="pg_160"/> crew into boats immediately, later sent master
                    back with German boarding party. Sank ship with bombs 30 minutes after torpedo.
                    No offer assistance. Sea moderate, wind light, sky overcast, boats picked up
                    midnight by admiralty vessel, no deaths or injuries. One American aboard, Martin
                    Feldman, 1714 South Fifth Street, Philadelphia. Have joint affidavit Feldman and
                    officers. This message to Ambassador, Consul General.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
